<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Camping respawn points is a lamer tactic</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:21 p.m. 16/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Camping respawn points is a lamer tactic<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1909" TARGET=_self>Weird way to play</A> (Baahi)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Almost all of us on the PvP server are against this form of lamer tactic. Unless of course you were a complete lamer yourself and were slaughtering newbies of your own race and wantonly looting them. There really is little or no justification for such behavior. Months ago I sent a request to Verant that the default respawn points be moved within range of the guards or placed back inside the towns. No action was taken on this issue to date.
<P>If you are not too soured on the experience, try getting a higher level player to rebind you closer to the guards. That should solve the problem, at least for your character.
<P>&gt; I initially started my first (and second) player char on the PvP
<BR>&gt; server, because this I believed was the most fun and realistic
<BR>&gt; way to play! Much to my dismay i found that some players saw it
<BR>&gt; as their ultimate job tojust ruin the game for others! I several
<BR>&gt; times experienced that a large party of players would camp at a
<BR>&gt; respawn point to kill players that reappeared after being killed
<BR>&gt; somewhere else! Now what is the fun in standing around casting a
<BR>&gt; root spell on a defenseless char without any EQ and then just
<BR>&gt; hack him to bits. After being killed this way 6 times in a row i
<BR>&gt; decided that it simply wasnt worth the effort (also got so
<BR>&gt; infuriated that i deleted a char that i had put a lot of time
<BR>&gt; and effort into) to play PvP and have now moved on to greener
<BR>&gt; pastures on another server where people enjoy the roleplaying
<BR>&gt; aspects of the game as much as the hack and slash! If I was to
<BR>&gt; ever try my luck again i would suggest haveing some guards close
<BR>&gt; to the respawn points to guard against such cases.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
